main event: Two circular, tapering objects, about the size of a softball, were sighted at Hickam AFB, Hawaii. The objects had no tail, with a light orange top and a white bottom, traveling at speeds in excess of 500 miles per hour.
interesting points: The objects were observed by Major ----- USF rated pilot and Mrs ----- housewife, suggesting multiple credible witnesses.
The objects were seen at two different positions at different altitudes within a five-minute interval, displaying good maneuverability.
There were no sound or exhaust trails associated with the objects.
The first sighting indicated a northernly direction, while the second sighting involved a 25-degree dive.
The altitude of the first sighting was estimated to be 6-7,000 feet, and the second sighting involved a dive beginning at 9-10,000 feet, with the object disappearing behind a cloud.
witnesses: Major ----- USF rated pilot and Mrs ----- housewife
